# Interpreter for ___session_dump0 - Session database dump
#
# The session dump function generates executable shell commands for recreating
# named sessions. It produces output for capture/piping.
#
# Type: Non-terminal function (produces data for consumption by other commands)
# Default: cat (output to stdout for capture/piping)
#
# Usage:
#   vpn-switch session dump > session-backup.sh  # Save session-only dump
#   vpn-switch dump > full-backup.sh             # Full dump (calls session dump)
#
# Override examples:
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_session_dump=tee /tmp/session-dump.log  # Output and log
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_session_dump=cat  # Default (explicit)
#
# Note: This is called by ___dump0, which handles the prologue/epilogue.
# The session dump focuses only on session-specific commands (named sessions).
